args:
The prince hears the first Mitsuhide betrayed
the first Nobunagaâ€”but the current namesakes
overcame that ancestral enmity. As they explain
the relationship between their clans, Ebisu is
ensnared, but manages to escape. The whole
party then pursues him to the Kagura Stage.
Ha ha ha! Take that, fish!
What a divine piece of seafood!\nSurely Ebisu would love to sink\nhis nasty fangs into this.
Maybe we should take a nibble first\nto be certain. Or else... Hmm...
It is what we call a heavenly gleamshard,\nalthough I expect your people know it\nby a different name.
Yeah, we call them otherworld fragments.\nWhere did you find this?
That fish we caught spit it out.\nMaybe it ate it or something?
Heavenly gleamshards are extraordinarily\nvaluable. I doubt one would be left lying\naround where a fish could get at it.
Perhaps Ebisu dropped one of our stolen\ngleamshards in his haste to escape.
That means he was in this very spot!
Give it here. I wish to smell it.\n*sniff* *sniiiiff*
This still smells clearly of Ebisu.\nHe can't have gone far.
Then let's hurry up and use the fish\nto lure him back!
Do you actually think this is gonna work?
It has been working well enough so far.\nPerhaps we should give the plan a chaâ€”
Oh, this isn't working at ALL!
Fishin' up the bait was easy enough,\nbut if we can't actually fish up the cat,\nit ain't gonna count for much.
Is ï¼‚fishing up a catï¼‚ even a thing?
I could have sworn that it was.
Are you feeling all right, Cleo?
If this plan doesn't work, we'll be...\nUuurgggh... M-my stomach...
He's right. Heck, maybe we should all take\na cue from Lady Mitsuhide and take a nap.\nIsn't that right, master? ...Er, master?
Hey, wait. Where did she go?\nAnd where's Lady Nobunaga?
I'll see if I can find them.
Hey, so what's the deal with the faerie who\nfollows {player_name} around?
That is Notte. She and His Majesty have\nbeen bosom companions for an age.
Why couldn't you just let me nap in peace?\nIt's not like I ASKED you to follow me all\nthe way out here to Alberia.
This is no time for sleep!\nWe must ready for WAR!
This could be the last time you and I are\nable to travel to a foreign land together,\nand we must make the most of it!
Er, is there something you want to do\ntogether that we can only do abroad?
All right, fine. We'll take a nap together.\nIf we snooze the day away in a foreign\nland, we can both get what we want.
Growing girls need their sleep, right?\nHere, lie down beside me.

What, pray, do you hope to accomplish by
sleeping the day away? It certainly cannot
be further growth, as you are nearly a
woman grown already.
Hush it! Maybe I'm just a late bloomer.
Anyway, I'm tired of you questioning me.\nEither lie down and shut your yapper,\nor else just leave me alone.
If you are so weary of me, I would have\nyou draw your weapon and cut me down!
I need both of you to take a deep breath\nand just calm down for a second.
Yeah! Fighting each other isn't gonna\naccomplish anything!
I'm pretty sure challenging someone to\nï¼‚cut you downï¼‚ counts as fighting.
Puh-leeze. This is a squabble. A spat.\nA big nothing. We've fought worse than\nthat in our sleep.
Wait, really? Oh, man, sorry.\nSounds like we overreacted there.
But if I'm honest, it's sorta surprising\nhow well you two actually get along.\nYou seem like total opposites!

Well, we've known each other forever and
worked through some pretty heavy stuff.
Things like that make it easy to trust
another person.
Yep. And it all started when\nMitsuhide killed Nobunaga.
Wait, you killed her? Whaaaaa...?\nOhmigosh, dude, are you a GHOST?!
I'm not talking about that Nobunagaâ€”\nI'm talking about the FIRST Nobunaga.
So a long time ago, my Mouse Clan\nserved under Nobunaga's Horse Clan.
Everyone expected the Mouse Wyrmclan\nto back Nobunaga for shogun in order to\nraise their own status.
But the Mouse leader, Mitsuhide, betrayed\nNobunaga and attacked their ally instead.
No one knows. Apparently the old\nNobunaga and Mitsuhide got along\nfamously and trusted each other.

Anyway, as you can imagine, that little
incident has put somewhat of a damper on
relations between the Mouse and Horse
Clans, even after all these years.
But you guys are total BFFs!

That's 'cause neither of us give a crap
about tradition. I mean, is there anything
more stupid than having a mortal enemy
locked in before you're even BORN?
Forming one's allies and enemies is a\ndecision of vital importance, and I will\nreserve such judgments for myself!
Man, you guys have VERY different\npersonalities, but at least you think alike!
So that's how you were able to overcome\nthe past and forge a relationship youâ€”
Hold up. You guys hear that?\nSounds like quite the to-do!
Perhaps our allies have ensnared Ebisu.\nCome, Mitsuhide! We ride!
OWWWW! Stop pulling my ear, jerk!\nYou're gonna yank it clean off my head\nif you keep doing that!
We caught him! We caught Ebisu!
You used fish to trick me? HISSSSS!\nLooks like it's time for me to leave.
MRAAAAAWR! Get away from my tail!
I WILL NOT LET YOU BEST ME,\nNO MATTER HOW CUTE YOU MAY BE!
Uh oh. This one's got the crazy eyes...
All that pent-up stress is burstin' out!
I can barely recognize him now.\n...Er, should we do something?
Oh, I'll NEVER give it backâ€”because\nthen I'll never get my satisfaction!
The Kagura Stage awaits!\nBye-onara, suckers! Meooow!
He's gonna escape to the otherworld!
You'll not get away, fiend!\nMy life depends on this!
Chase him down and slice him to ribbons!
All right, I'm comingâ€”although I can't\nhelp but wonder what Ebisu's side of\nthis particular story sounds like.
It isn't enough to just recover the gifts;\nwe need to figure out WHY he did this.
And that means we'll have to\nfollow him to the Kagura Stage!
